{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:53:16.029Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Byte-Pair Encoding (BPE) is the subword tokenization algorithm behind GPT, Llama, and many production LLM vocabularies. It starts with bytes or characters and iteratively merges the most frequent adjacent pairs into new tokens, building a vocabulary that balances compression and coverage. Agent developers working with OpenAI, open-weight GPT-style models, or custom tokenizers routinely encounter BPE."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "BPE training loop: iterative pair merging and inference steps"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "BPE begins with a base vocabulary of individual bytes or characters. It scans training text, counts adjacent symbol pairs, merges the most frequent pair into a new symbol, and repeats until reaching a target vocabulary size. The result is a merge table applied deterministically at inference: repeatedly merge the highest-priority known pairs in each word."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "BPE solves the open-vocabulary problem \u2014 rare words decompose into known subword pieces instead of mapping to unknown tokens. For agents, BPE determines how code, JSON, URLs, and multilingual text compress into tokens, directly affecting context consumption, cost, and whether specific strings fit in prompts."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No unknown tokens for most text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 any string decomposes into subwords or bytes"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Efficient for English and code", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 common patterns become single tokens"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Deterministic encoding", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 same merge rules always produce same tokens"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Widely supported", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 tiktoken, Hugging Face, Rust tokenizers"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Vocabulary and merges are training-corpus dependent \u2014 domain mismatch hurts compression"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inconsistent tokenization of numbers and whitespace across BPE variants"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Not inherently multilingual-optimal unless trained on diverse corpora"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merge table must ship with the model \u2014 cannot swap without re-embedding"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it works"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training loop (simplified): initialize symbols, count pairs, merge most frequent, add merged symbol to vocabulary, repeat."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Initial:  l o w e r _\nCounts:   (\"l\",\"o\")=1, (\"o\",\"w\")=1, (\"w\",\"e\")=1, (\"e\",\"r\")=1, (\"r\",\"_\")=1\nMerge 1:  lo w e r _     -> vocabulary gains \"lo\"\nMerge 2:  lo w e r _     -> if (\"lo\",\"w\") most frequent, gain \"low\"\n...continues until vocab_size reached"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inference applies merges in priority order (rank) from the trained merge table:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from tokenizers import Tokenizer\nfrom tokenizers.models import BPE\n\n# Load a pretrained BPE tokenizer (GPT-2 style)\ntokenizer = Tokenizer.from_pretrained(\"gpt2\")\n\ntext = '{\"tool\": \"search\", \"query\": \"BPE tokenization\"}'\nencoding = tokenizer.encode(text)\nprint(encoding.tokens)\nprint(encoding.ids)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use it"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "BPE tokenization applies automatically when using GPT-family models, many open LLMs, and Claude (modified BPE). Inspect BPE behavior when optimizing JSON tool schemas, counting tokens for code-heavy agents, or training custom models with Hugging Face tokenizers."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Examples"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The string \"tokenization\" might merge as [\"token\", \"ization\"] while \"Tokenization\" splits differently due to capitalization. JSON keys like \"user_id\" often become repeated subword patterns \u2014 designing shorter keys saves tokens in high-volume agent calls."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Real-world example"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "An agent sends 50KB JSON telemetry blobs in prompts. BPE tokenizes numeric arrays into many small tokens. The team switches to base64-compressed summaries, reducing token count from 18,000 to 4,200 \u2014 directly enabled by understanding BPE's handling of digits and punctuation."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Assuming BPE splits on whitespace \u2014 merges cross space boundaries unpredictably"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training a custom BPE on English-only data for a multilingual agent"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Changing merge rules without retraining embeddings from scratch"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inspect token splits for your domain's high-frequency strings (tool names, JSON keys)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use official tokenizer libraries rather than approximating BPE manually"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When training custom models, include representative agent prompts in tokenizer training corpus"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparison with alternatives"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "WordPiece (BERT) selects merges by likelihood rather than frequency. SentencePiece treats input as raw Unicode stream with configurable whitespace handling. BPE remains the dominant choice for autoregressive LLMs used in agent stacks."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "BPE is zip compression for text \u2014 repeatedly fuse the most common letter-pairs into shortcuts until you have a fixed dictionary of allowed pieces."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "BPE builds vocabularies by iteratively merging frequent symbol pairs"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GPT and many open LLMs use BPE \u2014 it shapes agent token costs"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rare words split into subwords; byte fallback handles anything else"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Always test domain-specific strings with the model's BPE tokenizer"}]}]}]}]}}